{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_0162Ln7uPA69kGHUcBvbxQjk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ROOT CAUSE: `src/be_strlib.c:497-560` — `str_format` has no handling for the `%%` escape (literal `%`). After `get_mode` advances past the `%`, `*p` is `'%'`, but before the `switch` the code unconditionally enforces `if (index > top) be_raise(...)`. So `s.format(\"%%\")` (top=1, index=2) raises \"bad argument #2 to 'format': no value\" instead of emitting a literal `%`. Even if an argument were supplied, control would fall into the `default` branch and raise \"invalid option '%%'\". Compare with `be_pushvfstr` (line 170+) which correctly handles `%%` with `format = p + 2`.\n\nLOCAL FIX: In `str_format`, handle `%%` before consuming an argument. Replace the block starting at line 514 with:\n\n```c\nbuf[0] = '\\0';\nif (*p == '%') {                    /* literal %% */\n    be_pushstring(vm, \"%\");\n    concat2(vm);\n    format = p + 1;\n    continue;                       /* do not advance index */\n}\nif (index > top) {\n    be_raise(vm, \"runtime_error\", be_pushfstring(vm,\n        \"bad argument #%d to 'format': no value\", index));\n}\nswitch (*p) { ... }\n```\n\n(Equivalently, add `case '%': be_pushstring(vm, \"%\"); break;` to the switch and skip the `++index` / `index>top` check when `*p=='%'`.)\n\nGLOBAL FIX: Eliminate the duplicated, hand-rolled format parser. `str_format` and `be_pushvfstr` both walk a printf-style format string with subtly different rules (`be_pushvfstr` handles `%%`, `str_format` doesn't; each has its own type-conversion table). Factor the format-string scan into a single helper that yields tokens (`LITERAL`, `PERCENT`, `SPEC(kind, modeStr)`) and have both call sites consume those tokens. A token-driven design makes the literal-`%` case a first-class state and forces every conversion specifier (including future ones like `%q`, `%b`) to be added in exactly one place, structurally preventing \"missing specifier\" / \"specifier consumes argument it shouldn't\" bugs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1212,"cache_read_input_tokens":29743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1212},"output_tokens":47,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8aba79c3-bad6-4dcc-a83d-0f1efec59ec7","uuid":"8b85e8e3-132e-4acc-898a-215b6fae25e8"}
